      "comment": "SUMMER HAIL (8) recorded a Bottom Up - Grade 5 win two back then missed the frame last time at this track, but drawn Box 8 this time where she has two wins. This looks easier and expected to bounce back. MISS JECKELL (1) turned in a modest effort most recently when sixth at this track over 350m behind Choji Akimichi (19.77) in a Grade 5. Cannot be underestimated. PUNCH DRUNK LOVE (4) has been hard to follow lately, running fourth (17.01) last time but prior to that ran very well when placed at Ballarat. Can turn it around this time. BULLSEYE BOB (6) is in winning form and worth including in the main hopes.",
